                <p>这一页介绍可证伪，即弗洛伊德发觉自己的解释没有被患者接受时，就说患者有很强的阻抗，是患者拒绝承认自身的症状。</p><blockquote>the experience of reflectionis the only criterion for the corroboration or failure of hypotheses. If it does not come about, there is still an alternative: either the interpretation is false(that is, the theory or its application to a given case) or, to the contrary, the resistances, which have been correctly diagnosed, are too strong.</blockquote><p>另外，这意味着成败其实是单方面的</p><blockquote>Here success and failure cannot be intersubjectivelyestablished</blockquote><p>intersubjectively被翻译成主体通性，我只能说太渣了</p>
