              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                <p>作者终于开始评论弗洛伊德</p><blockquote>The energy-distribution model only creates the semblance that psychoanalytic statements are about measurable transformations of energy. Not a single statement about quantitative relations derived from the conception of instinctual economics has ever been tested experimentally.</blockquote><p>弗的能量模型(力比多)在讲能量描述，但并没有实证的研究</p><p>中译：</p><blockquote>受到了实验检验的唯一陈述</blockquote><p>254页：</p><blockquote>自然科学的方法论，在它的自我反思阶段上能够揭示出语言同工具活动之间的特殊联系</blockquote><p>英译版是：</p><blockquote>At the level of its self-reflection, the methodology of the natural sciences takes cognizanceof a specific connection between language and instrumental action, comprehends it as an objective structure, and defines its transcendentalrole. </blockquote><p>这里instrumental action被翻译成了工具活动，说明翻译没有查过wiki</p><p>wiki: Actions explained by reasoning about means are often called "instrumentally rational." They are supposed to be efficient means or tools for achieving consequences.</p><p>wiki说instrumental action是效率导向的(区别于道德规范)</p><p>所以正确的译法应该是：自然科学之方法，在于揭示语言和效率导向行为的关系</p><p></p><p>256</p><blockquote>It derives its force from confusing the logic of the public usage of languageby means of semantically false identifications. </blockquote><blockquote>它的力量的获得是由于它通过语义学上错误的等同化打乱了社会语言使用的逻辑</blockquote><p>这一段在解释症状作为一种语言，虽然已经失去了语法结构，但还有其内容。这种内容不能被理解，但可以使用自我id和本我ego进行解读(这是在介绍弗洛伊德的观点)</p><p>257</p><blockquote>Metapsychology deals with just as fundamental a connection: the connection between language deformation and behavioral pathology.</blockquote><p>元心理解决语言歪曲和行为病态的联系</p><p>258</p><blockquote>不过，被称为前提的元心理学允许对历史的东西作系统的概括，它提供语言畸形化和行为病理学联系的范畴和基本假定的命题</blockquote><p>英译：</p><blockquote>Only the metapsychology that is presupposed allows the systematic generalization of what otherwise would remainpure history</blockquote><p>可见systematic generalization，系统性推广，被错误翻译成了“概括”</p><blockquote>The general interpretations developed in this framework are the result of numerous and repeated clinical ex