              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                <p>分析性的观点只有当它们被分析者作为认识接受之后，才对分析者有价值</p><p>英译版：</p><blockquote>analytic insights possess validity for the analyst only after they have been acceptedas knowledge by the analysand himself.</blockquote><p>英译版显然说得更清楚：分析师认为这个解释有validity，是因为他自己接受了这个观点</p><blockquote>For the empirical accuracy of general interpretations depends not on controlled observation and subsequent communicationamong investigators but rather on the accomplishment of self-reflection and subsequent communication between the investigator and his "object."</blockquote><p>弗洛伊德理论的empirical accuracy并不在于观察、研究者的讨论，而在于内省、分析师和来访者的沟通——这就是在说，弗洛伊德其实是inaccurate</p><p>虽然第十章花费了大量篇幅介绍弗洛伊德的理论，作者对于弗洛伊德其实是不认可的</p><p>当然，新精神分析不在讨论范围</p>
